  "text": "Since we anticipated good response to TKI therapy, we decided to treat our patient with crizotinib directly as first-line therapy. Up to now there are, however, only limited data on this drug as a first-line treatment in ROS1-translocated tumors. To the best of our knowledge, only 7 patients have been reported so far [CITATION_1] who all responded to that treatment. These data and our findings might provide a rationale for first-line crizotinib treatment of ROS1-positive tumors in clinical trials.",
